---
title: One-Pan Shrimp Lo Mein with Udon Noodles, Green Beans, and Carrots
description: Udon noodles lend themselves naturally to stir-frys. Because they’re thick and chewy, they do a great job of soaking up the sauce (here, that’s a mix of hoisin and soy). All that’s needed to make a recipe like this complete is a mix of veggies and a hearty protein; we’re providing you with crisp green beans, crunchy carrot, and perfectly plump shrimp.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5a1f3b44ad1d6c4d4d6c5ef2-752ab2b6.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-shrimp-lo-mein-5a1f3b44ad1d6c4d4d6c5ef2-9e170cee.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 520 kcal
  fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 71 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 28 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1480 mg
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-shrimp-lo-mein-5a1f3b44ad1d6c4d4d6c5ef2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Cut @green beans{6%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Peel @ginger{1%thumb}, then mince until you have 1 TBSP. Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}.

> TIP: Set aside some of the scallion greens for garnish, if you like.

Peel @carrot{1%unit}, then cut in half lengthwise. Slice each half into thin half-moons.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a large, tall-sided pan over medium-high heat. Add green beans and toss until softened slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add carrot and toss until both are fully tender, ~{3-4%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

While veggies cook, stir together @soy sauce{1%tablespoon}, @organic veggie stock{1%unit}, @hoisin sauce{1%tablespoon} (we sent more), @sugar{2%tsp}, and @water{1/4%cup} in a #small bowl{}.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} and pat dry with a #paper towel{}. Add shrimp, ginger, scallions, and garlic to pan with veggies. Cook, tossing, until shrimp are nearly opaque and firm, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir sauce into pan and let reduce slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add @udon noodles{8%ounce} and cook, tossing frequently, until tender and chewy, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: If noodles won't loosen up or sauce seems dry, add a splash of water.

Season with salt and pepper. Divide lo mein between bowls, sprinkle with reserved scallion greens (if using), and serve.